result.name: OVO Cafe

reviews.text: Nice deco and great choices of salad, main dishes and drinks. suitable for vegetarian or on diet's friends. wish they can have more seats.
Environment is so beautiful. Feel relaxing have lunch here. Food options was limited. All the food are vegetarian.

My family had an appointment at 6pm for celebration of my brother’s birthday, when we arrived that day, the waitress told us that someone had make a block booking and the restaurant was not available until 6:30pm. What’s the point of making an appointment if you already have someone block booking? Or if they suddenly walked in and took over the whole place, would you mind to please contact us before we arrive?

We can wait for half an hour but on a special day this is ruining the mood, I’m sorry but I can’t give a better rating based on that. We do like vegetarian food that’s why we picked OvoCafe.

The two stars are the wonderful decorations and interior design.

It says they close at 22:00 but when I arrived more than 30 minutes before 22:00 but they said “last order is 9” and wouldn’t take my order. I traveled there from my hotel in Kowloon. Waste of my evening!

I hate to give them a bad review because I’ve eaten here before and the food was great. But cutting people off more than 30 minutes before closing time is rude. Change your public hours to 9PM if that’s when you really close.

Also beware: cash only
such a dumb policy these days; it's so easy to take credit cards. Maybe they are cash-only to avoid paying taxes.
Love this place whenever I could drop by. Fantastic food and adorable relaxing environment.
